title: Cross Country Competes at Greater Louisville Classic
text: Cross Country Competes at Greater Louisville Classic North Florida Athletics Eden Meyer had solid performances Saturday in the highly competitive Greater Louisville Classic at E.P. Tom Sawyer State Park.In a field full of regional and nationally ranked squads, the Ospreys placed 19th over the 8k layout that will serve as the host course for the NCAA Championships. Junior Bradley Langenberg , who posted a personal best 26:04.Iona claimed the team title with Michigan, Louisville, Ole Miss and Illinois wrapping up the top five squads."This was a real eye opening meet for our guys," said head coach Jeff Pigg . "There was some fierce competition from a lot of good teams. I feel like we learned some things and will be much more prepared in the future. (Mike) Damato ran a solid race and (Tyler) Bennett also ran well again. Hopefully, we can get a couple of our guys back in our lineup soon."In addition to the men's team, Meyer ran as an individual in the women's 5k race earning a 45th-place showing with a season best 17:39 clocking."Eden had a very solid day," added Pigg. "I feel like this was definitely a growth experience for her to race against such high level competitors."North Florida will be off for a couple weeks before closing out the regular season schedule on Oct. 16 at the Crimson Classic in Tuscaloosa, Ala.
